4.00	Abraham_Firkovich	Abraham Firkovich	Abraham (Avraham) ben Samuel Firkovich (1786–1874) was a famous leader of the Qarays (Crimean Karaites). He was born in Lutsk, Volhynia, then lived in Lithuania, and finally settled in Çufut Qale, Crimea. Firkovich was a communal leader and hakham. He is best known as a collector of manuscripts and amateur archeologist. In Karaite circles he is sometimes known by the acronym "ABen ReSheF" (from "Abraham ben Rabbi Shemuel Firkovich").	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f6/Ruman_Firkovichphoto.jpg
